<i>May only good things fill your life</i>

582
00:33:48,131 --> 00:33:50,200
<i>That's all you need to wish for</i>

583
00:34:00,377 --> 00:34:02,145
Hype Na Jeong.

584
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:04,848
I've got high hopes for you.

585
00:34:06,316 --> 00:34:07,985
Since it took so much
for you to come back,

586
00:34:08,485 --> 00:34:10,554
you'll have to work twice,
even three times harder than others.

587
00:34:12,189 --> 00:34:13,390
Okay, let's head back.

588
00:34:13,390 --> 00:34:14,191
Executive Director.

589
00:34:14,191 --> 00:34:16,093
Yeah, what is it?

590
00:34:24,368 --> 00:34:25,302
You have to go?

591
00:34:27,070 --> 00:34:28,405
I'm sorry.

592
00:34:28,405 --> 00:34:30,207
My schedule got a bit mixed up,
so I should.

593
00:34:40,651 --> 00:34:41,551
You're leaving already?

594
00:34:43,887 --> 00:34:44,821
Yeah.

595
00:34:48,659 --> 00:34:49,893
Then go ahead.

596
00:34:50,827 --> 00:34:54,731
If she can't even stay
until the end of a team dinner,

597
00:34:54,731 --> 00:34:55,799
why did she bother coming back to work?

598
00:35:16,820 --> 00:35:19,022
Why do I have to be sent
to the study room?

599
00:35:19,022 --> 00:35:21,325
If I blow this exam,
are you going to take responsibility?

600
00:35:22,092 --> 00:35:24,261
Why are you so touchy?

601
00:35:24,261 --> 00:35:27,097
If my friend's busy, I can watch her kids.

602
00:35:27,497 --> 00:35:29,866
Your daughter's in exam season,
and your friend comes first?

603
00:35:30,367 --> 00:35:32,970
If she has to dump her kids at someone
else's place, then she shouldn't work.

604
00:35:32,970 --> 00:35:34,504
She's so selfish.

605
00:35:37,307 --> 00:35:39,109
Do you think you can just say
whatever you want?

606
00:35:44,748 --> 00:35:45,949
Bo Hyeon.

607
00:36:00,030 --> 00:36:01,398
I'm sorry, Na Jeong.

608
00:36:02,899 --> 00:36:05,435
Bo Hyeon's going through
puberty these days,

609
00:36:05,435 --> 00:36:07,004
and she argues about everything.

610
00:36:08,071 --> 00:36:08,906
No.

611
00:36:09,940 --> 00:36:11,308
I'm the one who should apologize.

612
00:36:12,743 --> 00:36:13,911
I was being clueless.

613
00:36:14,311 --> 00:36:16,179
I didn't even know
it was exam week for Bo Hyeon.

614
00:36:16,380 --> 00:36:18,515
Hey, don't worry about it.

615
00:36:18,949 --> 00:36:20,784
She doesn't study anyway,

616
00:36:20,784 --> 00:36:23,086
and she just found the perfect excuse,
that's all.

617
00:36:28,692 --> 00:36:30,627
You haven't even had dinner yet?

618
00:36:31,628 --> 00:36:32,663
I have.

619
00:36:33,497 --> 00:36:35,032
Hey, eat before you go.

620
00:36:35,032 --> 00:36:36,500
No, Jin Hee. I'm not hungry.

621
00:36:36,500 --> 00:36:39,436
I made too much curry.
If it's left, I'll have to throw it out.

622
00:36:39,436 --> 00:36:41,271
Consider this
helping me not to waste food.

623
00:36:58,755 --> 00:37:00,424
It must be tough for you.

624
00:37:10,701 --> 00:37:13,604
Did you buy a new dish?

625
00:37:14,471 --> 00:37:15,639
I haven't seen this before.

626
00:37:25,849 --> 00:37:26,817
Na Jeong.

627
00:37:37,761 --> 00:37:38,962
Still, Na Jeong,

628
00:37:39,830 --> 00:37:41,932
hang in there as long as you can.

629
00:37:43,600 --> 00:37:46,303
If you hold out a bit longer
and the kids get older,

630
00:37:47,170 --> 00:37:49,706
you'll be glad you stuck it out
when you look back.

631
00:37:51,575 --> 00:37:54,912
You know, when I had Bo Hyeon
and quit my job,

632
00:37:55,612 --> 00:37:58,215
it was really hard.

633
00:37:59,249 --> 00:38:01,685
But do you know what the hardest part was?

634
00:38:05,222 --> 00:38:07,658
Feeling pushed out of society.

635
00:38:09,393 --> 00:38:11,528
That was what I couldn't stand.

636
00:38:18,802 --> 00:38:21,905
But you grabbed the opportunity
before it was too late.

637
00:38:23,373 --> 00:38:25,642
It's such a precious opportunity.

638
00:38:25,842 --> 00:38:26,777
So hold on.

639
00:38:27,177 --> 00:38:29,012
Hold on as long as you can.

640
00:38:29,446 --> 00:38:33,850
I didn't begrudgingly watch
Min Woo and Min Jun, you know.

641
00:38:33,850 --> 00:38:37,454
In a way, you're living out my dream.

642
00:38:37,454 --> 00:38:38,322
Okay?

643
00:38:38,322 --> 00:38:41,792
So how could I not root for you?

644
00:38:43,694 --> 00:38:45,262
And the Cho Na Jeong I know...

645
00:38:45,729 --> 00:38:48,732
isn't someone who crumbles
just because of something like this.

646
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:51,435
Chin up, Cho Na Jeong.

647
00:38:56,139 --> 00:38:57,674
Eat up.

648
00:38:57,674 --> 00:38:59,543
It won't taste good once it's cold.

649
00:39:03,614 --> 00:39:04,748
Come on, eat up.

650
00:39:09,019 --> 00:39:10,053
Thanks, Jin Hee.

