655
00:40:22,526 --> 00:40:23,393
Ye Na.

656
00:40:25,028 --> 00:40:26,496
Did you get home okay last night?

657
00:40:26,496 --> 00:40:27,631
It ran really late, didn't it?

658
00:40:28,332 --> 00:40:29,499
Did you prep for the meeting?

659
00:40:29,499 --> 00:40:31,368
Of course. Let's go.

660
00:40:34,738 --> 00:40:35,606
Here.

661
00:40:38,942 --> 00:40:40,377
What's this?

662
00:40:40,377 --> 00:40:42,346
You got me a latte? That's fattening.

663
00:40:43,547 --> 00:40:46,850
Haven't you noticed
I only drink regular coffee?

664
00:40:46,850 --> 00:40:48,018
Sorry.

665
00:40:48,585 --> 00:40:51,421
You haven't been eating much lately,

666
00:40:51,421 --> 00:40:53,190
so I was worried your stomach would hurt.
I'll bring you another drink.

667
00:40:53,190 --> 00:40:54,157
It's fine.

668
00:40:56,260 --> 00:40:58,328
Have you thought of any ideas?

669
00:40:59,196 --> 00:41:01,465
You must've gotten
a lot of input while at home.

670
00:41:02,099 --> 00:41:03,967
While I was home,

671
00:41:03,967 --> 00:41:06,003
there was a product I looked into.

672
00:41:06,003 --> 00:41:07,504
An automatic stationary bike.

673
00:41:07,771 --> 00:41:10,040
You just rest your feet on the pedals...

674
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:11,241
and it moves on its own.

675
00:41:11,241 --> 00:41:13,277
Who would buy that?

676
00:41:13,877 --> 00:41:16,079
If you use an automatic bike,

677
00:41:16,079 --> 00:41:17,547
how is that a workout?

678
00:41:17,547 --> 00:41:19,316
Hear me out first.

679
00:41:19,316 --> 00:41:21,885
My mom had knee surgery a few years ago,

680
00:41:21,885 --> 00:41:24,288
and did rehab for a while.

681
00:41:24,288 --> 00:41:27,491
For seniors with low strength,
it's really useful.

682
00:41:27,491 --> 00:41:30,661
Our home shopping's main customers
are older adults.

683
00:41:30,661 --> 00:41:31,561
I think...

684
00:41:31,561 --> 00:41:32,863
this is not impressive.

685
00:41:33,130 --> 00:41:36,667
The Executive Director said
we should lower our target age.

686
00:41:37,367 --> 00:41:40,370
We'd be better off with luxury bags,
sunglasses, and things like that.

687
00:41:40,370 --> 00:41:42,706
No, sunglasses are a no-go.

688
00:41:43,974 --> 00:41:44,908
Why?

689
00:41:44,908 --> 00:41:46,643
No matter how nice they are,

690
00:41:46,643 --> 00:41:49,680
you can't tell if they suit you
without trying them on.

691
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:51,982
If returns pour in, that's just risk.

692
00:41:52,816 --> 00:41:54,318
That's your view, Na Jeong.

693
00:41:54,318 --> 00:41:56,119
That's not the trend these days.

694
00:41:56,587 --> 00:41:58,922
You don't have any useful ideas.

695
00:42:10,233 --> 00:42:11,168
All right.

696
00:42:11,902 --> 00:42:14,071
Let's wrap up the monthly meeting here.

697
00:42:15,105 --> 00:42:16,440
And now,

698
00:42:16,740 --> 00:42:19,376
let me hear items you think
would be good...

699
00:42:19,376 --> 00:42:20,377
to launch on our channel.

700
00:42:23,046 --> 00:42:24,348
Speak up, everyone.

701
00:42:26,283 --> 00:42:28,118
On first-mover products,

702
00:42:28,118 --> 00:42:30,454
reports say we're far behind
our competitors.

703
00:42:30,988 --> 00:42:33,590
We all need to take ownership
and work together to survive.

704
00:42:36,593 --> 00:42:37,561
Executive Director.

705
00:42:37,794 --> 00:42:40,163
May my mentee present something?

706
00:42:41,198 --> 00:42:42,065
Who's your mentee?

707
00:42:42,466 --> 00:42:43,233
Me.

708
00:42:45,535 --> 00:42:47,437
I'm Yang Mi Sook.

709
00:42:48,939 --> 00:42:49,873
Go ahead.

710
00:42:50,140 --> 00:42:52,276
I may not know much else,

711
00:42:52,276 --> 00:42:55,712
but I'm pretty savvy with luxury,
so here's my take.

712
00:42:55,979 --> 00:42:57,648
This season,

713
00:42:57,648 --> 00:42:59,716
Hercules released a new sunglasses model.

714
00:43:00,117 --> 00:43:01,385
- Put it up.
- Yes.

715
00:43:03,186 --> 00:43:04,087
Nice.

716
00:43:04,955 --> 00:43:06,490
Really sleek, right?

717
00:43:07,090 --> 00:43:10,060
It sold out completely
as soon as it dropped.

718
00:43:10,827 --> 00:43:13,196
Before another home shopping channel
gets exclusivity,

719
00:43:13,196 --> 00:43:16,133
how about we lock it in first?

720
00:43:16,767 --> 00:43:17,734
I am...

721
00:43:18,535 --> 00:43:19,903
against it.

722
00:43:21,138 --> 00:43:23,640
No matter how luxurious
and pretty sunglasses are,

723
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:24,741
without trying them on,

724
00:43:24,741 --> 00:43:26,944
you cannot tell...

725
00:43:26,944 --> 00:43:28,278
if they suit you.

726
00:43:28,946 --> 00:43:31,148
If customers buy them just because
they're pretty and the return rate rises,

727
00:43:31,348 --> 00:43:32,783
that could pose a serious risk.

728
00:43:35,085 --> 00:43:37,020
Instead, I've got a product...

729
00:43:37,020 --> 00:43:39,022
I have a strong hunch about.

730
00:43:39,923 --> 00:43:42,059
An automatic stationary bike.

731
00:43:45,662 --> 00:43:46,463
Show us.

732
00:43:48,699 --> 00:43:50,500
You rest your feet on the pedals,

733
00:43:50,500 --> 00:43:52,903
and it moves them automatically.

734
00:43:52,903 --> 00:43:53,804
Automatically?

735
00:43:54,638 --> 00:43:55,472
I'm not sure.

736
00:43:55,839 --> 00:43:57,608
Who would buy a bike
that doesn't even require working out?

737
00:43:59,042 --> 00:44:01,178
Most seniors who've had knee surgery...

738
00:44:01,178 --> 00:44:02,346
receive rehabilitation therapy...

739
00:44:02,346 --> 00:44:04,414
that moves the legs for them...

740
00:44:04,414 --> 00:44:06,283
after the procedure.

741
00:44:06,283 --> 00:44:09,119
And they know how effective it is.

742
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:13,156
As you know,
older customers' buying power

743
00:44:13,156 --> 00:44:14,358
in home shopping is no joke.

744
00:44:17,194 --> 00:44:19,263
Okay, fair point.

745
00:44:19,997 --> 00:44:21,732
Mr. Choi, reach out to the vendor.

746
00:44:23,033 --> 00:44:25,135
And like Ms. Song,

747
00:44:25,135 --> 00:44:26,603
don't limit yourselves
to your lane, everyone.

748
00:44:26,603 --> 00:44:29,206
If you've got good items, speak up.

749
00:44:29,206 --> 00:44:30,340
Yes, understood.

750
00:44:37,981 --> 00:44:39,016
Hey.

751
00:44:39,016 --> 00:44:40,951
Don't you think that was too much?

752
00:44:40,951 --> 00:44:43,453
The automatic stationary bike was my idea.

753
00:44:43,453 --> 00:44:44,755
Why did you talk like it was yours?

754
00:44:45,222 --> 00:44:46,990
What are you saying?

755
00:44:46,990 --> 00:44:48,692
Are you calling me a thief?

756
00:44:49,059 --> 00:44:51,695
What's so great
about some little idea from an intern?

757
00:44:52,029 --> 00:44:54,698
And it was the team's idea,
not yours alone.

758
00:44:54,698 --> 00:44:57,100
What? "Some little idea?"

759
00:44:57,100 --> 00:44:59,436
Can you even come up with one yourself?

760
00:44:59,803 --> 00:45:00,938
What did you just say?

761
00:45:01,772 --> 00:45:03,006
I knew it.

762
00:45:03,006 --> 00:45:05,242
Weren't you the one
who asked me to help you out?

763
00:45:05,242 --> 00:45:07,044
I'm not letting this slide.

764
00:45:07,044 --> 00:45:09,613
I'll mark you for insubordination
in the mentee review,

765
00:45:09,613 --> 00:45:10,714
so get ready to be fired.

766
00:45:12,049 --> 00:45:13,517
And you think I'll just sit still?

767
00:45:14,017 --> 00:45:16,086
Run your filthy mouth one more time,

768
00:45:16,086 --> 00:45:18,455
and you'll be reported
for workplace bullying.

769
00:45:19,456 --> 00:45:21,758
And about when you lied to me
that it was a hair product...

770
00:45:21,758 --> 00:45:23,694
to dump it on me.

771
00:45:24,294 --> 00:45:26,063
You think I didn't notice?

772
00:45:30,634 --> 00:45:31,802
She's out of her mind.

773
00:45:31,802 --> 00:45:33,937
She's crazy!

774
00:45:37,241 --> 00:45:38,108
Song Ye Na.

775
00:45:38,909 --> 00:45:41,311
You dare poke the bear?

776
00:45:42,279 --> 00:45:43,981
You're dead now.

777
00:45:44,348 --> 00:45:45,682
- Mr. Choi.
- Yes?

778
00:45:46,917 --> 00:45:48,885
How are we supposed to sell those?

779
00:45:48,885 --> 00:45:51,822
We can't even swap in
something else as a decoy.

780
00:45:53,991 --> 00:45:55,092
So,

781
00:45:55,092 --> 00:45:56,927
how ripe are the apples right now?

782
00:45:57,961 --> 00:45:59,129
They're still green.

783
00:45:59,329 --> 00:46:02,065
We scheduled the broadcast
to align with the shipment,

784
00:46:02,065 --> 00:46:03,066
but because of the abnormal
weather...

785
00:46:03,066 --> 00:46:05,235
Then what do you want us to do?

786
00:46:05,235 --> 00:46:07,604
Go live from a studio
with nothing to show?

787
00:46:07,604 --> 00:46:10,540
Just say
it's a "pre-order, ships later" product?

788
00:46:10,540 --> 00:46:13,410
How will we make them order?

789
00:46:13,410 --> 00:46:14,244
Producer Kim.

790
00:46:14,478 --> 00:46:15,612
How about this?

791
00:46:15,846 --> 00:46:18,615
We do the broadcast from the orchard.

792
00:46:18,615 --> 00:46:20,918
Then we don't need
to switch to another product,

793
00:46:20,918 --> 00:46:23,020
and it will also look pretty convincing.

794
00:46:23,020 --> 00:46:24,521
We can stress...

795
00:46:24,521 --> 00:46:27,257
that we'll ship fresh, in-season fruit
right after harvest, building trust.

796
00:46:27,457 --> 00:46:28,625
That sounds good.

797
00:46:28,625 --> 00:46:29,793
What do you think?
What do you think, Producer Choi?

798
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:32,062
Fresh, in-season fruit.

799
00:46:32,062 --> 00:46:33,797
That's actually not a bad idea.

800
00:46:33,797 --> 00:46:34,698
Right?

801
00:46:34,698 --> 00:46:37,367
What's good about it?

802
00:46:37,367 --> 00:46:39,369
You want us to go
all the way out of town just for that?

803
00:46:39,670 --> 00:46:42,372
No way. Find another option.

804
00:46:43,340 --> 00:46:46,510
Then do you have a better idea?

805
00:46:46,910 --> 00:46:49,079
Right now, that seems like our best shot.

806
00:46:49,079 --> 00:46:51,648
Yeah. We don't really have
an alternative at the moment.

807
00:46:52,049 --> 00:46:54,585
Or do you have any?

808
00:46:57,054 --> 00:47:00,324
I'm trying to think of one.

809
00:47:00,324 --> 00:47:01,525
We can figure it out later.

810
00:47:01,525 --> 00:47:03,827
Later? We don't have time for later.

811
00:47:03,827 --> 00:47:05,462
Let's just go there and do it.

812
00:47:05,462 --> 00:47:07,798
Mr. Choi, coordinate the schedule
with the supplier and let me know.

813
00:47:07,798 --> 00:47:09,066
Yes, sir.

814
00:47:09,066 --> 00:47:10,634
Fresh, in-season fruit.

815
00:47:10,834 --> 00:47:11,702
Good idea.

